Qtum Logo
Qtum is a hybrid platform that combines elements of both Bitcoin and Ethereum Qtum was the first to combine the value transfer functionality of Bitcoin (BTC) and the smart contract support of Ethereum (ETH) into a single platform. This allows users to build applications running on a blockchain, while also allowing their creations to transact in a way that’s similar to Bitcoin. The QTUM cryptocurrency is used to pay fees and provide governance on the platform.
You can download theQtumlogo on full-version of the page.

Qantas Airlines Logo
Qantas Airways Limited (/ˈkwɒntəs/) is the flag carrier of Australia and its largest airline by fleet size, international flights and international destinations. It is the third oldest airline in the world, after KLM and Avianca having been founded in November 1920; it began international passenger flights in May 1935. The Qantas name comes from “QANTAS”, an acronym for its original name, “Queensland and Northern Territory Aerial Services”, and it is nicknamed “The Flying Kangaroo”.
You can download theQantas Airlineslogo on full-version of the page.
